260
00:11:28.844 --> 00:11:30.742
but I tried to join the church,

261
00:11:30.742 --> 00:11:32.610
the Episcopal Church in Scarsdale,

262
00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:34.544
to say is any of this true?

263
00:11:34.544 --> 00:11:35.913
No, they didn't know.

264
00:11:35.913 --> 00:11:38.048
Then I tried it at Bryn Mawr College.

265
00:11:38.048 --> 00:11:40.417
Can you ask a question, the future of humanity,

266
00:11:40.417 --> 00:11:43.360
where are we going, what is each of our vocation?

267
00:11:43.360 --> 00:11:44.922
Couldn't ask the question

268
00:11:44.922 --> 00:11:47.291
because all the disciplines are separate.

269
00:11:47.291 --> 00:11:50.227
Then I met President Eisenhower through my father.

270
00:11:50.227 --> 00:11:53.063
1952, go into the Oval Office.

271
00:11:53.063 --> 00:11:55.459
Mr. President I have a question for you.

272
00:11:55.459 --> 00:11:56.733
Yes, young lady?

273
00:11:56.733 --> 00:11:58.836
I'd like to know, do you know the meaning

274
00:11:58.836 --> 00:12:01.271
of our new power, that's good?

275
00:12:01.271 --> 00:12:04.571
Where is the United States going with this power?

276
00:12:04.571 --> 00:12:07.310
It was after the atomic bomb.

277
00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:11.815
It was just at the beginning of this huge sense

278
00:12:11.815 --> 00:12:13.918
of our own power.

279
00:12:13.918 --> 00:12:17.221
But I could tell that it could destroy us

280
00:12:17.221 --> 00:12:19.557
and I thought the President might know.

281
00:12:19.557 --> 00:12:22.896
Of course he had no, he said "I have no idea."

282
00:12:22.896 --> 00:12:25.629
So then, I married an artist and I think

283
00:12:25.629 --> 00:12:28.499
my first shift point was when Earl,

284
00:12:28.499 --> 00:12:32.403
my husband that I'd married, said to me

285
00:12:32.403 --> 00:12:35.673
"Until the artist knows the new story,

286
00:12:35.673 --> 00:12:38.742
"And can see an image of humans commensurate

287
00:12:38.742 --> 00:12:41.312
"With our power to shape the future,

288
00:12:41.312 --> 00:12:42.913
"We won't be able to do it."

289
00:12:42.913 --> 00:12:45.165
<v Regina>No wonder you married him.</v>

290
00:12:45.165 --> 00:12:47.064
<v ->I thought, I'm gonna marry him,</v>

291
00:12:47.064 --> 00:12:48.383
it was in my junior year abroad--

292
00:12:48.383 --> 00:12:49.818
<v Regina>That's amazing!</v>
<v Barbara>And I did.</v>

293
00:12:49.818 --> 00:12:52.059
<v Regina>What an amazingly profound statement</v>

294
00:12:52.059 --> 00:12:53.591
for what you were looking for.

295
00:12:53.591 --> 00:12:55.258
Two souls waiting to connect.

296
00:12:55.258 --> 00:12:56.527
<v ->So here's something just to note,</v>

297
00:12:56.527 --> 00:12:58.230
if you have a sense of mission

298
00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:01.482
that's very deep inside you, notice.

299
00:13:01.482 --> 00:13:02.212
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

300
00:13:02.212 --> 00:13:03.834
<v ->If you're getting a signal of somebody</v>

301
00:13:03.834 --> 00:13:05.269
that is part of that mission

302
00:13:05.269 --> 00:13:07.171
and you're part of that person's mission.

303
00:13:07.171 --> 00:13:09.273
Because in order to evolve these days

304
00:13:09.273 --> 00:13:12.843
you actually have to have very specific partnerships.

305
00:13:12.843 --> 00:13:13.743
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

306
00:13:13.743 --> 00:13:16.647
<v ->It is not just random networking anymore,</v>

307
00:13:16.647 --> 00:13:18.316
cuz we're in metamorphosis.

308
00:13:18.316 --> 00:13:20.184
But I didn't know that then.

309
00:13:20.184 --> 00:13:22.752
So, when we got married,

310
00:13:22.752 --> 00:13:24.721
I had five children.

311
00:13:24.721 --> 00:13:26.723
Lost the question for some time.

312
00:13:26.723 --> 00:13:28.659
Got depressed.

313
00:13:28.659 --> 00:13:32.560
Began to think that there was something wrong with me.

314
00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:36.099
Because I loved my children, I loved my husband,

315
00:13:36.099 --> 00:13:38.512
I lived in Lakeville, Connecticut.

316
00:13:38.512 --> 00:13:40.638
So, I went to the local psychiatrist.

317
00:13:40.638 --> 00:13:43.974
And as a woman, that I wanted more,

318
00:13:43.974 --> 00:13:45.510
thought more was coming,

319
00:13:45.510 --> 00:13:47.411
I had a greater role to play,

320
00:13:47.411 --> 00:13:51.480
and the analysis was you're neurotic. (laughs)

321
00:13:51.480 --> 00:13:52.783
<v Regina>Because you wanted more</v>

322
00:13:52.783 --> 00:13:55.170
than what the structure was--

323
00:13:55.170 --> 00:13:57.518
<v ->With five children and a house and a nice husband?</v>

324
00:13:57.521 --> 00:14:00.157
What in the world is wrong with you, Barbara?

325
00:14:00.157 --> 00:14:04.281
So, I then read Abraham Maslow,

326
00:14:04.281 --> 00:14:06.181
that was another point,

327
00:14:06.181 --> 00:14:08.499
Toward a Psychology of Being.

328
00:14:08.499 --> 00:14:12.080
Maslow said when he studied wellness, not sickness,

329
00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:15.306
every fully-functioning, joyful person

330
00:14:15.306 --> 00:14:18.909
had one thing in common, chosen vocation.

331
00:14:18.909 --> 00:14:23.867
Chosen work, they found intrinsically self-rewarding.

332
00:14:23.867 --> 00:14:25.383
And of service.

333
00:14:25.383 --> 00:14:27.851
So, I realized I loved my children,

334
00:14:27.851 --> 00:14:30.454
but motherhood was not my vocation.

335
00:14:30.454 --> 00:14:33.023
that's a really shocking thing in the late 50's.

336
00:14:33.023 --> 00:14:34.224
<v Regina>Yes, yes!</v>

337
00:14:34.224 --> 00:14:35.826
<v ->Early 60's.</v>

338
00:14:35.826 --> 00:14:38.029
But the depression instead of then

339
00:14:38.029 --> 00:14:40.497
being something wrong with me,

340
00:14:40.497 --> 00:14:43.067
was a pressure to express.

341
00:14:43.067 --> 00:14:45.302
That's a very important thing for a woman.

342
00:14:45.302 --> 00:14:47.438
Now we know this much better.

343
00:14:47.438 --> 00:14:49.207
But there's still many women,

344
00:14:49.207 --> 00:14:52.609
who don't fully allow what's inside them

345
00:14:52.609 --> 00:14:54.598
to be fully expressed.

346
00:14:54.598 --> 00:14:58.541
So, I was just seeking how to do that.

347
00:14:58.541 --> 00:15:02.586
And I think the next point in my life that was so important,

348
00:15:02.586 --> 00:15:05.355
was meeting Dr. Jonas Salk.

349
00:15:05.355 --> 00:15:07.424
And I wrote a letter, like I was very bold,

350
00:15:07.424 --> 00:15:09.559
I just would reach out because I now knew

351
00:15:09.559 --> 00:15:11.292
I had to find my vocation.

352
00:15:11.292 --> 00:15:12.529
<v Regina>That's one of the most inspirational</v>

353
00:15:12.529 --> 00:15:13.631
parts of you, by the way,

354
00:15:13.631 --> 00:15:16.167
that you have the nerve to even do these things.

355
00:15:16.167 --> 00:15:19.002
<v ->So, I write to Abraham Maslow, ask him to lunch.</v>

356
00:15:19.002 --> 00:15:21.205
I wrote to Jonas Salk about his theater,

357
00:15:21.205 --> 00:15:23.941
theater of man, I made it up what it should be,

358
00:15:23.941 --> 00:15:26.277
the evolutionary story and so on.

359
00:15:26.277 --> 00:15:29.036
And he called me up one day,

360
00:15:29.036 --> 00:15:30.747
I had just had my fifth child.

361
00:15:30.747 --> 00:15:31.581
I'll never forget it,

362
00:15:31.581 --> 00:15:34.540
it was in the fall of 1964 in New England.

363
00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:37.522
You know, the beautiful days, and the apple orchard

364
00:15:37.522 --> 00:15:41.292
and all the trees turning yellow and golden.

365
00:15:41.292 --> 00:15:42.860
And the phone rang and he said

366
00:15:42.860 --> 00:15:46.163
"Mrs. Hubbard, this is Jonas Salk.

367
00:15:46.163 --> 00:15:48.432
"I have just read your letter,

368
00:15:48.432 --> 00:15:52.103
"And you have expressed my dream better than I could.

369
00:15:52.103 --> 00:15:55.707
"We are two peas in the same genetic pod.

370
00:15:55.707 --> 00:15:57.441
"Can I take you to lunch?"

371
00:15:57.441 --> 00:15:58.740
<v Regina>Isn't that amazing?</v>

372
00:15:58.740 --> 00:16:00.544
<v ->Now what happened, this is in the journey</v>

373
00:16:00.544 --> 00:16:04.306
of an evolutionary woman,

374
00:16:04.306 --> 00:16:05.946
evolutionary person,

375
00:16:05.946 --> 00:16:09.138
is I had never met anybody

376
00:16:09.138 --> 00:16:11.348
who had the same coding

377
00:16:11.348 --> 00:16:14.457
of the sense of what's emergent.

378
00:16:14.457 --> 00:16:17.995
It was considered neurotic in the Freudian analysis.

379
00:16:17.995 --> 00:16:21.164
In exurbia you're supposed to be content.

380
00:16:21.164 --> 00:16:23.500
And we were supposed to be content,

381
00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:25.935
and when I wasn't, I felt guilty.

382
00:16:25.935 --> 00:16:27.643
What was wrong with me?

383
00:16:27.643 --> 00:16:29.974
So, he came and took me out to lunch.

384
00:16:29.974 --> 00:16:31.908
And as he was opening the door,

385
00:16:31.908 --> 00:16:35.221
and it was this beautiful fall day,

386
00:16:35.221 --> 00:16:37.281
and he said "This is the garden of Eden."

387
00:16:37.281 --> 00:16:40.581
And I said "Yes, I'm Eve and I'm leaving."

388
00:16:41.351 --> 00:16:44.264
I was going to leave

389
00:16:44.264 --> 00:16:46.334
the role I was in.

390
00:16:46.334 --> 00:16:50.994
I was going to leave the imprint

391
00:16:50.994 --> 00:16:53.264
of my cultural limitations.

392
00:16:53.264 --> 00:16:55.599
But I didn't know what it was.

393
00:16:55.599 --> 00:16:59.006
And when he drove me to New York from Connecticut,

394
00:16:59.006 --> 00:17:00.604
the thing that he did which I think

395
00:17:00.604 --> 00:17:02.373
every evolutionary person needs,

396
00:17:02.373 --> 00:17:04.208
but particularly women,

397
00:17:04.208 --> 00:17:08.264
he said, I told him what was wrong with me.

398
00:17:08.264 --> 00:17:10.842
Desire for the future.

399
00:17:10.842 --> 00:17:12.215
And I thought something great might happen,

400
00:17:12.215 --> 00:17:13.734
and I had something to do about it.

401
00:17:13.734 --> 00:17:14.594
<v Regina>(laughing)</v>

402
00:17:14.594 --> 00:17:17.087
<v ->Oh, oy vey, how sick you must be!</v>

403
00:17:17.087 --> 00:17:20.392
And he said "Barbara, this is not what's wrong about you,

404
00:17:20.392 --> 00:17:23.136
"This is what is right about you.

405
00:17:23.136 --> 00:17:26.779
"You are an evolutionary mutant." (laughs)

406
00:17:26.779 --> 00:17:28.198
<v Regina>Yes, for the time.</v>
<v Barbara>Because in those</v>

407
00:17:28.198 --> 00:17:31.908
<v ->Days before all of this happened,</v>

408
00:17:31.908 --> 00:17:35.372
when a woman had this enormous sense of potentiality,

409
00:17:35.372 --> 00:17:37.841
she thought she was off base--

410
00:17:37.841 --> 00:17:38.508
<v Regina>Delusional.</v>

411
00:17:38.508 --> 00:17:39.844
<v ->Delusional!</v>

412
00:17:39.844 --> 00:17:43.382
So he said "I will introduce you

413
00:17:43.382 --> 00:17:45.162
"To three or four others."

414
00:17:45.162 --> 00:17:47.862
But the key was to be re-cognized.

415
00:17:47.862 --> 00:17:49.519
Recognized.

416
00:17:49.519 --> 00:17:53.819
For the essence of your being as what's emergent,

417
00:17:54.809 --> 00:17:57.929
rather than what's, oh just you know,

418
00:17:57.929 --> 00:18:01.948
your desire to do something or you're self-centered.

419
00:18:01.948 --> 00:18:03.880
No, it wasn't self-centered.

420
00:18:03.880 --> 00:18:06.302
So, I got totally empowered.

421
00:18:06.302 --> 00:18:10.507
And then I read, the next point was Teilhard de Chardin,

422
00:18:10.507 --> 00:18:13.544
the great Catholic Jesuit paleontologist,

423
00:18:13.544 --> 00:18:16.614
his book Toward a Psychology of Being.

424
00:18:16.614 --> 00:18:19.016
And in that book, this Catholic Jesuit,

425
00:18:19.016 --> 00:18:22.021
who'd never been published by the Church,

426
00:18:22.021 --> 00:18:26.942
experienced the Divine, the God Force, in matter.

427
00:18:26.942 --> 00:18:30.734
He said "Take away God, take away Christ, leave matter."

428
00:18:30.734 --> 00:18:33.964
Because he saw that the universal process of creation

429
00:18:33.964 --> 00:18:36.867
was coming up through energy, through matter,

430
00:18:36.867 --> 00:18:40.604
and he had this law of complexity consciousness.

431
00:18:40.604 --> 00:18:42.419
As systems become more complex,

432
00:18:42.419 --> 00:18:44.888
they jump in consciousness and freedom.

433
00:18:44.888 --> 00:18:47.744
And he saw we were moving towards the noosphere,

434
00:18:47.744 --> 00:18:50.714
connecting center with center, heat with heart.

435
00:18:50.714 --> 00:18:52.383
The thinking layer of earth

436
00:18:52.383 --> 00:18:56.186
made up out of TV, internet, telephones,

437
00:18:56.186 --> 00:18:58.879
communication, consciousness.

438
00:18:58.879 --> 00:19:02.426
And he talked about this great and wonderful event

439
00:19:02.426 --> 00:19:06.163
that would be the connectivity at the center

440
00:19:06.163 --> 00:19:09.849
of the core of our being's en masse.

441
00:19:09.849 --> 00:19:12.168
And that awakened in me

442
00:19:12.168 --> 00:19:16.073
the great thing I thought was coming. (laughs)

443
00:19:16.073 --> 00:19:17.274
<v Regina>You thought it was coming right away?</v>

444
00:19:17.274 --> 00:19:18.275
<v ->No.
<v Regina>Oh.</v>

445
00:19:18.275 --> 00:19:19.743
<v Barbara>I knew, I didn't know when.</v>

446
00:19:19.743 --> 00:19:20.510
<v Regina>Okay.</v>

447
00:19:20.510 --> 00:19:21.367
<v ->But when I read</v>

448
00:19:21.367 --> 00:19:24.785
from a scientific, spiritually-based point of view

449
00:19:24.785 --> 00:19:28.275
that earth itself was heading for a time

450
00:19:28.275 --> 00:19:31.488
of massive connectivity through the heart,

451
00:19:31.488 --> 00:19:34.524
and massive intelligence.

452
00:19:34.524 --> 00:19:35.843
So this was really in the--

453
00:19:35.843 --> 00:19:37.737
<v Regina>He was quite a visionary, yes.</v>

454
00:19:37.737 --> 00:19:40.897
<v ->But what I saw, what I felt really,</v>

455
00:19:40.897 --> 00:19:43.834
was that the vision that had motivated me,

456
00:19:43.834 --> 00:19:45.970
that something great wants to happen,

457
00:19:45.970 --> 00:19:47.738
that I'm somehow a part of it,

458
00:19:47.738 --> 00:19:51.569
that everybody's a part of it, got affirmed

459
00:19:51.569 --> 00:19:54.778
by Teilhard's vision of the omega,

460
00:19:54.778 --> 00:19:57.067
the noosphere coming together.

461
00:19:57.067 --> 00:19:59.149
And what happened was that the

462
00:19:59.149 --> 00:20:03.120
internal pressure to evolve and to express

463
00:20:03.120 --> 00:20:05.278
got affirmed

464
00:20:05.278 --> 00:20:08.298
at a spiritual and evolutionary level.

465
00:20:08.298 --> 00:20:11.295
Now there's one thing to go vertical to God,

466
00:20:11.295 --> 00:20:14.464
it's another thing to realize the process of creation

467
00:20:14.464 --> 00:20:16.600
is flowing through all of life.

468
00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:19.370
And that your desire to evolve,

469
00:20:19.370 --> 00:20:21.305
my desire to express,

470
00:20:21.305 --> 00:20:23.640
was the Divine force in me,

471
00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:26.009
was the universal process of creation.

472
00:20:26.009 --> 00:20:30.281
And when I got that I am the universe evolving,

473
00:20:30.281 --> 00:20:32.522
and so is everybody else,

474
00:20:32.522 --> 00:20:34.522
plus Jonas having affirmed

475
00:20:34.522 --> 00:20:39.456
this psychological need for expression and participation,

476
00:20:39.456 --> 00:20:42.025
I became an evolutionary woman.

477
00:20:42.025 --> 00:20:43.593
<v Regina>And you became one at a time,</v>

478
00:20:43.593 --> 00:20:45.132
you were really--
<v Barbara>Early 60's.</v>

479
00:20:45.132 --> 00:20:47.704
<v Regina>One of the first of this wave, really.</v>

480
00:20:47.704 --> 00:20:48.831
<v ->I was.
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

481
00:20:48.831 --> 00:20:50.367
<v Barbara>And another word for it I have is</v>

482
00:20:50.367 --> 00:20:53.470
a feminine co-creator.

483
00:20:53.470 --> 00:20:55.729
<v Regina>And this is really important now.</v>

484
00:20:55.729 --> 00:20:58.041
First, if you don't mind hopping next

485
00:20:58.041 --> 00:21:00.937
because I think coming after this was Sri Aurobindo?

486
00:21:00.937 --> 00:21:01.478
<v ->Yes.</v>

487
00:21:01.478 --> 00:21:02.172
<v Regina>And The Mother.</v>

488
00:21:02.172 --> 00:21:02.750
<v ->Yes.</v>

489
00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:04.072
<v Regina>Can you talk a little bit about that</v>

490
00:21:04.072 --> 00:21:06.316
and how that essentially fleshed out

491
00:21:06.316 --> 00:21:08.519
this understanding for you even more.

492
00:21:08.519 --> 00:21:09.586
<v ->Yes.</v>

493
00:21:09.586 --> 00:21:12.723
So, there was Maslow, Toward a Psychology of Being,

494
00:21:12.723 --> 00:21:14.846
everyone has chosen vocation.

495
00:21:14.846 --> 00:21:16.860
You've got to express your life purpose.

496
00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:19.004
Jonas recognizing

497
00:21:19.004 --> 00:21:22.364
the internal being as good.

498
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:25.369
The Teilhard de Chardin seeing God in evolution

499
00:21:25.369 --> 00:21:28.270
leading to omega.

500
00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:32.663
Then Aurobindo, I don't remember how I found it,

501
00:21:32.663 --> 00:21:36.038
but I found the book The Life Divine,

502
00:21:36.038 --> 00:21:37.908
which is his masterwork.

503
00:21:37.908 --> 00:21:40.084
And he traces what he calls

504
00:21:40.084 --> 00:21:43.421
the supramental intelligence of God,

505
00:21:43.421 --> 00:21:45.578
the consciousness force.

506
00:21:45.578 --> 00:21:50.227
And he thought it was dynamic, purposeful and directional.

507
00:21:50.227 --> 00:21:52.462
That the purpose of evolution

508
00:21:52.462 --> 00:21:55.232
was not to get off the wheel of life,

509
00:21:55.232 --> 00:21:58.268
it was not to dissolve into the one,

510
00:21:58.268 --> 00:22:02.038
but it was for that core of the spiral, as I think of it,

511
00:22:02.038 --> 00:22:04.041
that the consciousness force that came up

512
00:22:04.041 --> 00:22:05.408
through matter and life,

513
00:22:05.408 --> 00:22:08.279
was coming up through the great avatars.

514
00:22:08.279 --> 00:22:10.648
It was coming up through him.

515
00:22:10.648 --> 00:22:14.463
But he and The Mother together,

516
00:22:14.463 --> 00:22:17.540
could hold the space in consciousness.

