777
00:34:15.671 --> 00:34:17.813
But you know who's really out there?

778
00:34:17.813 --> 00:34:20.076
The ordinary folks.

779
00:34:20.076 --> 00:34:23.379
The millions of people who seem to be waking to empathy,

780
00:34:23.379 --> 00:34:26.015
to the internal desire, the women,

781
00:34:26.015 --> 00:34:28.552
desiring to express their unique purpose.

782
00:34:28.552 --> 00:34:31.019
They don't have to be a saint or an avatar

783
00:34:31.019 --> 00:34:33.223
to get that you're evolving.

784
00:34:33.223 --> 00:34:36.583
And I think the really...

785
00:34:36.583 --> 00:34:37.351
What is happening,

786
00:34:37.351 --> 00:34:41.406
I call it the evolutionary potential movement,

787
00:34:41.406 --> 00:34:42.931
is growing in every field.

788
00:34:42.931 --> 00:34:45.400
It's not just fixing problems,

789
00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:47.970
it's realizing new possibilities.

790
00:34:47.970 --> 00:34:49.672
And going back to the vision of this room

791
00:34:49.672 --> 00:34:51.041
with all the screens,

792
00:34:51.041 --> 00:34:54.977
the connectivity of all that creativity.

793
00:34:54.977 --> 00:34:55.545
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

794
00:34:55.545 --> 00:34:59.148
<v ->The non-linear, exponential creativity</v>

795
00:34:59.148 --> 00:35:04.103
of what's already there in itself is enough

796
00:35:04.103 --> 00:35:07.176
to make us aware of the emerging world.

797
00:35:07.176 --> 00:35:07.757
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

798
00:35:07.757 --> 00:35:10.826
<v ->We can survive, Bucky was right.</v>

799
00:35:10.826 --> 00:35:12.161
<v Regina>And you asked a question</v>

800
00:35:12.161 --> 00:35:16.398
in your talk earlier today, the response was interesting.

801
00:35:16.398 --> 00:35:19.302
You said let me see a show of hands,

802
00:35:19.302 --> 00:35:22.806
for all the women in the room who feel that you are,

803
00:35:22.806 --> 00:35:25.508
I don't remember the exact wording but essentially,

804
00:35:25.508 --> 00:35:28.063
you are part of this emerging,

805
00:35:28.063 --> 00:35:30.613
you are embodying or participating in this

806
00:35:30.613 --> 00:35:33.316
conscious evolution in some way.

807
00:35:33.316 --> 00:35:34.884
And I don't remember if you said through art or what,

808
00:35:34.884 --> 00:35:36.052
I don't think that was it,

809
00:35:36.052 --> 00:35:37.153
you can tell us what you said,

810
00:35:37.153 --> 00:35:40.657
but you asked that question and more than half

811
00:35:40.657 --> 00:35:42.793
of the women in the room raised their hand.

812
00:35:42.793 --> 00:35:45.881
Then you asked the exact same question of the men,

813
00:35:45.881 --> 00:35:48.864
do you feel that you're part of this emergence?

814
00:35:48.864 --> 00:35:51.934
And only I think two or three, from where I could see,

815
00:35:51.934 --> 00:35:55.093
only a half a dozen or less men raised their hand.

816
00:35:55.093 --> 00:35:57.373
That was very interesting.

817
00:35:57.373 --> 00:35:59.243
Tell us what that phenomena is.

818
00:35:59.243 --> 00:36:02.625
<v ->Well, I've noticed as a woman and a mother,</v>

819
00:36:02.625 --> 00:36:06.183
is that the shift from procreation

820
00:36:06.183 --> 00:36:07.884
and the yearning to reproduce

821
00:36:07.884 --> 00:36:09.552
and to give birth through your body

822
00:36:09.552 --> 00:36:11.821
and to hold the newborn child

823
00:36:11.821 --> 00:36:14.790
and to nurse it, and love it and give your life for it,

824
00:36:14.790 --> 00:36:17.626
that's programmed into our hormones.

825
00:36:17.626 --> 00:36:19.729
When the women got the signal,

826
00:36:19.729 --> 00:36:21.163
not only through the feminist movement

827
00:36:21.163 --> 00:36:22.698
but through the environmental movement

828
00:36:22.698 --> 00:36:23.799
and to the reality

829
00:36:23.799 --> 00:36:27.236
of the planetary overloading of population,

830
00:36:27.236 --> 00:36:29.573
one more doubling, we're out.

831
00:36:29.573 --> 00:36:33.710
Women began to wake up and to evolve.

832
00:36:33.710 --> 00:36:35.111
I think of it like this,

833
00:36:35.111 --> 00:36:39.248
the desire for procreation and nurturing of the child

834
00:36:39.248 --> 00:36:42.418
into the desire for self-expression,

835
00:36:42.418 --> 00:36:45.555
and from self-reproduction to self-evolution.

836
00:36:45.555 --> 00:36:47.823
And women started to be awakened

837
00:36:47.823 --> 00:36:50.226
to their own creativity.

838
00:36:50.226 --> 00:36:53.330
To their own inner spiritual creativity.

839
00:36:53.330 --> 00:36:54.930
Not just my profession is,

840
00:36:54.930 --> 00:36:56.899
or how I can get to be equal to men

841
00:36:56.899 --> 00:36:58.934
in a dysfunctional world.

842
00:36:58.934 --> 00:37:01.870
It's not to get to the top of the glass ceiling.

843
00:37:01.870 --> 00:37:06.571
It's actually to express, and I felt and asked

844
00:37:07.431 --> 00:37:09.711
that women are giving birth

845
00:37:09.711 --> 00:37:12.583
to the authentic feminine self.

846
00:37:12.583 --> 00:37:17.162
That there's a new phase, particularly for women over 50,

847
00:37:17.162 --> 00:37:20.056
50, 60, 70, I'm 80!

848
00:37:20.056 --> 00:37:23.259
I call it regenopause.

849
00:37:23.259 --> 00:37:24.160
<v Regina>I love that term.</v>

850
00:37:24.160 --> 00:37:27.697
<v ->The pause where your body is aging,</v>

851
00:37:27.697 --> 00:37:30.365
the whole thing after menopause we're aging and dying,

852
00:37:30.365 --> 00:37:32.502
but actually you're rising.

853
00:37:32.502 --> 00:37:35.071
Because your spirituality, your creativity,

854
00:37:35.071 --> 00:37:37.173
in women over 50!

855
00:37:37.173 --> 00:37:40.744
Women 50 used to be old!

856
00:37:40.744 --> 00:37:42.579
Women over 50, I think of it like this,

857
00:37:42.579 --> 00:37:44.747
the body may be aging but this is going like this

858
00:37:44.747 --> 00:37:48.451
and the body gets confused. (laughs)

859
00:37:48.451 --> 00:37:49.819
<v Regina>And starts re-patterning itself.</v>

860
00:37:49.819 --> 00:37:52.354
<v ->And it starts to re-pattern because look at me,</v>

861
00:37:52.354 --> 00:37:55.547
I actually feel new.

862
00:37:55.547 --> 00:37:56.259
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

863
00:37:56.259 --> 00:38:00.330
<v ->Not aging, or saging, or youthing.</v>

864
00:38:00.330 --> 00:38:01.263
<v Regina>That's a critical distinction--</v>

865
00:38:01.263 --> 00:38:02.531
<v ->But I feel emergent.</v>

866
00:38:02.531 --> 00:38:03.700
<v Regina>Yes, exactly.</v>

867
00:38:03.700 --> 00:38:06.135
<v ->So, I asked the women</v>

868
00:38:06.135 --> 00:38:08.787
how many of you feel

869
00:38:08.787 --> 00:38:11.227
that something is emerging in you?

870
00:38:11.227 --> 00:38:13.976
And most of them were over 50 in this audience.

871
00:38:13.976 --> 00:38:16.378
That something is emerging in you that's creative

872
00:38:16.378 --> 00:38:20.675
that hasn't yet fully expressed itself.

873
00:38:20.675 --> 00:38:22.652
Everybody, including me.

874
00:38:22.652 --> 00:38:24.420
Why is that?

875
00:38:24.420 --> 00:38:27.590
I think it's because we're designed to give birth,

876
00:38:27.590 --> 00:38:31.026
and we're not gonna give birth to many babies,

877
00:38:31.026 --> 00:38:33.339
and the women over 50,

878
00:38:33.339 --> 00:38:35.164
no more eggs, we are the egg.

879
00:38:35.164 --> 00:38:36.198
<v Regina>Yeah, we are the egg.</v>

880
00:38:36.198 --> 00:38:38.601
<v ->We are the egg and what we're giving birth to</v>

881
00:38:38.601 --> 00:38:41.873
in our authentic feminine self, is the creative self.

882
00:38:41.873 --> 00:38:42.738
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

883
00:38:42.738 --> 00:38:46.235
<v ->And it doesn't wanna create more of the same.</v>

884
00:38:46.235 --> 00:38:48.579
And so the very same unconditional love

885
00:38:48.579 --> 00:38:51.146
that would give a woman the ability

886
00:38:51.146 --> 00:38:52.515
to go through the pain of birth

887
00:38:52.515 --> 00:38:55.284
and love that child no matter what,

888
00:38:55.284 --> 00:38:59.688
gives the feminine a love of the unknown world.

889
00:38:59.688 --> 00:39:03.959
And the willingness to give herself into her vocation,

890
00:39:03.959 --> 00:39:07.496
and I call it vocational arousal.

891
00:39:07.496 --> 00:39:11.601
It's the same thing as sexual arousal at the next level.

892
00:39:11.601 --> 00:39:15.071
<v Regina>Yes and that does make a lot of sense.</v>

893
00:39:15.071 --> 00:39:17.206
I mean, just looking at it from a very basic level

894
00:39:17.206 --> 00:39:18.607
of every woman who's given birth

895
00:39:18.607 --> 00:39:22.713
understanding this sense of high creativity,

896
00:39:22.713 --> 00:39:26.849
unpredictability, an expectation to embrace someone

897
00:39:26.849 --> 00:39:28.150
you've never met before.

898
00:39:28.150 --> 00:39:30.252
You don't know what this being's bringing into your world,

899
00:39:30.252 --> 00:39:32.188
but you're totally, you know intuitively

900
00:39:32.188 --> 00:39:34.489
that you're committed to this journey.

901
00:39:34.489 --> 00:39:37.760
And to take that, take the babies out of it, (laughs)

902
00:39:37.760 --> 00:39:39.161
the hormones out of it,

903
00:39:39.161 --> 00:39:43.199
and still embody that same inner quest

904
00:39:43.199 --> 00:39:44.866
makes perfect sense.

905
00:39:44.866 --> 00:39:47.517
<v ->And this willingness to not know--</v>

906
00:39:47.517 --> 00:39:48.967
<v Regina>Yes!</v>

907
00:39:48.967 --> 00:39:51.008
<v ->Even who you are yet.</v>

908
00:39:51.008 --> 00:39:51.508
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

909
00:39:51.508 --> 00:39:52.944
<v ->And it's so interesting if a woman</v>

910
00:39:52.944 --> 00:39:57.134
60 or 70 years old says to me

911
00:39:58.284 --> 00:40:01.183
"I'm not sure what I'm becoming."

912
00:40:01.183 --> 00:40:03.920
It's one thing, it was bad enough for me to say it at 30,

913
00:40:03.920 --> 00:40:07.723
but 60 or 70, or 80 for that matter,

914
00:40:07.723 --> 00:40:11.694
to be still emergent and not exactly sure.

915
00:40:11.694 --> 00:40:15.527
Now I call this vocational arousal.

916
00:40:15.527 --> 00:40:16.883
Being the life pulse,

917
00:40:16.883 --> 00:40:21.470
the impulse of evolution arising as you, your expression,

918
00:40:21.470 --> 00:40:24.774
and you have to follow a compass of joy.

919
00:40:24.774 --> 00:40:27.523
Because there's nobody out there to tell you

920
00:40:27.523 --> 00:40:29.412
this is what you need to do.

921
00:40:29.412 --> 00:40:31.864
<v Regina>Has to be your resonance, yes.</v>

922
00:40:31.864 --> 00:40:33.983
<v ->And because these vocations</v>

923
00:40:33.983 --> 00:40:36.485
usually don't yet have a label,

924
00:40:36.485 --> 00:40:38.978
they don't have, you don't go to school for them,

925
00:40:38.978 --> 00:40:40.822
and usually there's no pay.

926
00:40:40.822 --> 00:40:43.626
You have to become entrepreneurial.

927
00:40:43.626 --> 00:40:46.328
You have to become co-creative.

928
00:40:46.328 --> 00:40:49.098
You have got to find partners.

929
00:40:49.098 --> 00:40:51.434
And when you find a partner,

930
00:40:51.434 --> 00:40:54.737
that somehow your vocational arousal

931
00:40:54.737 --> 00:40:58.475
excites that partner, and that partner's creativity

932
00:40:58.475 --> 00:41:01.610
excites your vocational arousal

933
00:41:01.610 --> 00:41:05.281
and you feel that maybe by joining, becoming a team,

934
00:41:05.281 --> 00:41:08.283
that you could better fulfill each of you,

935
00:41:08.283 --> 00:41:11.964
you get suprasexual excitement! (laughs)

936
00:41:11.964 --> 00:41:13.589
<v Regina>I was going to ask you about that,</v>

937
00:41:13.589 --> 00:41:16.191
I love going from Sri Aurobindo's supermental

938
00:41:16.191 --> 00:41:18.527
to your suprasexual.

939
00:41:18.527 --> 00:41:19.962
<v ->That's a really good jump, isn't it?</v>

940
00:41:19.962 --> 00:41:21.347
<v Regina>It is a good jump.</v>

941
00:41:21.347 --> 00:41:22.864
But I wanted you to make that leap

942
00:41:22.864 --> 00:41:25.057
because what we're talking about is

943
00:41:25.057 --> 00:41:28.938
the emergence of an entirely new type of connection

944
00:41:28.938 --> 00:41:31.833
between human beings, between men and women,

945
00:41:31.833 --> 00:41:34.110
in friendship, a new kind of partnership

946
00:41:34.110 --> 00:41:37.079
that really has not been given birth to

947
00:41:37.079 --> 00:41:38.381
until this period of time.

948
00:41:38.381 --> 00:41:40.088
Not very often, anyway.

949
00:41:40.088 --> 00:41:42.751
<v ->When it happens spontaneously, you're really fortunate.</v>

950
00:41:42.751 --> 00:41:45.363
And between men and women in the past,

951
00:41:45.363 --> 00:41:47.023
very, very difficult.

952
00:41:47.023 --> 00:41:49.925
The women were programmed into a different role,

953
00:41:49.925 --> 00:41:54.730
certainly marriage, remember the old phrase wedlock?

954
00:41:54.730 --> 00:41:57.199
The bonds of marriage?

955
00:41:57.199 --> 00:41:59.868
I got married in '51, that was the ceremony

956
00:41:59.868 --> 00:42:01.237
Today when people do get married,

957
00:42:01.237 --> 00:42:02.938
they make up their own vows.

958
00:42:02.938 --> 00:42:04.407
Most women wouldn't say that.

959
00:42:04.407 --> 00:42:06.575
<v Regina>Right.</v>

960
00:42:06.575 --> 00:42:08.411
No less the obey portion.

961
00:42:08.411 --> 00:42:09.778
<v ->Obey!</v>

962
00:42:09.778 --> 00:42:11.833
You see, it's changed.

963
00:42:11.833 --> 00:42:13.482
We have to say in the last 50 years,

964
00:42:13.482 --> 00:42:17.213
a huge shift in the feminine consciousness.

965
00:42:18.063 --> 00:42:21.524
What I sense is that when the feminine

966
00:42:21.524 --> 00:42:24.126
begins to turn on to her deeper life purpose,

967
00:42:24.126 --> 00:42:27.730
her vocation, it's an unknown quantity

968
00:42:27.730 --> 00:42:30.926
because it doesn't have the job, the label,

969
00:42:30.926 --> 00:42:33.370
it's not a professional status often.

970
00:42:33.370 --> 00:42:37.206
She may be very professional in her capability, or not.

971
00:42:37.206 --> 00:42:39.808
See I just graduated from motherhood

972
00:42:39.808 --> 00:42:41.464
to being an evolutionary.

973
00:42:41.464 --> 00:42:44.080
I didn't have a professional period,

974
00:42:44.080 --> 00:42:47.399
which is, in a way a loss, because it would have been good.

975
00:42:47.399 --> 00:42:49.285
But I had 20 years of five children,

976
00:42:49.285 --> 00:42:52.521
so my profession was motherhood.

977
00:42:52.521 --> 00:42:55.858
Then I jumped to being an evolutionary woman.

978
00:42:55.858 --> 00:42:58.560
So, the women, I believe,

979
00:42:58.560 --> 00:43:02.131
have vocational arousal en masse,

980
00:43:02.131 --> 00:43:04.934
that when they say yes to it,

981
00:43:04.934 --> 00:43:07.469
and they follow that inner compass,

982
00:43:07.469 --> 00:43:11.495
they seek their partners and they can be...

983
00:43:11.495 --> 00:43:14.443
It's not homosexual, bisexual, transsexual,

984
00:43:14.443 --> 00:43:16.245
it's suprasexual.

985
00:43:16.245 --> 00:43:17.846
So, I think we don't need

986
00:43:17.846 --> 00:43:20.349
to come out of the closet as gay or straight,

987
00:43:20.349 --> 00:43:23.351
but come out of the closet as whole. (laughs)

988
00:43:23.351 --> 00:43:25.221
<v Regina>Yes. (laughs)</v>

989
00:43:25.221 --> 00:43:29.898
<v ->Come out of the closet as what I call a universal human.</v>

990
00:43:29.898 --> 00:43:34.325
So I'm a very young, universal human.

991
00:43:34.325 --> 00:43:35.831
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

992
00:43:35.831 --> 00:43:40.035
<v ->Joining millions of others, because we're all young</v>

993
00:43:40.035 --> 00:43:43.606
in that the culture that could fully receive us

994
00:43:43.606 --> 00:43:45.307
is what we have to create.

995
00:43:45.307 --> 00:43:46.742
<v Regine>Yes.</v>

996
00:43:46.742 --> 00:43:48.911
Let's talk men into this part of it now,

997
00:43:48.911 --> 00:43:50.713
that's the feminine part of it.

998
00:43:50.713 --> 00:43:52.380
What's happening with the men

999
00:43:52.380 --> 00:43:54.517
and how are they folding themselves

1000
00:43:54.517 --> 00:43:57.720
into this really completely new paradigm

1001
00:43:57.720 --> 00:44:00.656
from the way they've been experiencing their own life

1002
00:44:00.656 --> 00:44:04.486
and essentially creating their own lives?

1003
00:44:05.316 --> 00:44:08.831
<v ->In my experience, the best men I know</v>

1004
00:44:08.831 --> 00:44:11.600
are yearning for this to happen.

1005
00:44:11.600 --> 00:44:14.369
The best men in the world,

1006
00:44:14.369 --> 00:44:17.928
know that more of the same,

1007
00:44:17.928 --> 00:44:22.638
more of the same at the structural power center, will fail.

1008
00:44:23.088 --> 00:44:25.281
Even if they're in the power structure.

1009
00:44:25.281 --> 00:44:29.738
But the ones that have left being at the top of something,

1010
00:44:29.738 --> 00:44:31.520
who are seeking,

1011
00:44:31.520 --> 00:44:33.955
actually are much more confused than the women.

1012
00:44:33.955 --> 00:44:35.497
<v Regina>That's what I was going to ask,</v>

1013
00:44:35.497 --> 00:44:38.360
we're drawing upon something instinctive from the feminine.

1014
00:44:38.360 --> 00:44:38.885
<v ->Yes.</v>

1015
00:44:38.885 --> 00:44:42.064
<v Regina>What are they drawing upon, from your experience?</v>

1016
00:44:42.064 --> 00:44:43.098
<v ->See that's a very good point.</v>

1017
00:44:43.098 --> 00:44:46.468
The women, because we don't have a social pattern,

1018
00:44:46.468 --> 00:44:47.737
particularly for the older women

1019
00:44:47.737 --> 00:44:50.239
and the women who are not having children,

1020
00:44:50.239 --> 00:44:52.725
or who have very few children.

1021
00:44:52.725 --> 00:44:56.212
We don't have a cultural imprint to get over.

1022
00:44:56.212 --> 00:44:58.413
And the 50 or 60 years of the women's movement

1023
00:44:58.413 --> 00:45:02.785
had liberated us, but not just to be equal to men.

1024
00:45:02.785 --> 00:45:06.322
To be co-creators, that's what we're liberated to.

1025
00:45:06.322 --> 00:45:10.192
The men obviously have within them

1026
00:45:10.192 --> 00:45:13.496
their own essential spiritual creativity.

1027
00:45:13.496 --> 00:45:17.893
But the structures of the patriarchy and the success models

1028
00:45:17.893 --> 00:45:22.371
that men are trained to, make it harder for them.

1029
00:45:22.371 --> 00:45:24.940
And what really works for the men I have found,

1030
00:45:24.940 --> 00:45:26.891
and it's very tricky in here,

1031
00:45:26.891 --> 00:45:28.981
is if the woman

1032
